summary:
*loud, deep breath*
okay, so here's the motherfrickin' tea!☕ 
the etsy merchandise broke copyright policy.  that is LITERALLY...
body:
*loud, deep breath*

okay, so here’s the motherfrickin’ tea!☕

the etsy merchandise broke copyright policy. that is LITERALLY SOMETHING SOMEONE CAN SUE YOU FOR. it’s not just a “oooo taylor swift doesn’t care about her fans! she wants all the money to go to herself!!” copyright is a legitimate reason to sue someone, and taylor is FAR from the first person or company to do this. not to bring down another swiftie, but it’s the law. sorry.

the old guitar teacher was, surpise surprise, using taylor for clout. it wasn’t just him using her name in an “about me” paragraph. he didn’t just say somewhere on a page “oh, yeah, i taught taylor swift.” the domain of the website was itaughttaylorswift.com. taylor swift, although a person, is TRADEMARKED. you can’t use her name to promote your stuff. read the law. don’t be stupid. problem solved!

spotify basically WASN’T PAYING HER, or any other artist, for that matter. spotify paid less than a PENNY per play, and that money goes to the label, not the artist. taylor wasn’t making money, but people could still listen to her music that she worked so hard on. it wasn’t fair. taylor loves what she does, but it’s also her job. she has to make money.

and, get this, YOU DON’T HAVE TO BE A SOCIAL JUSTICE WARRIOR TO HELP PEOPLE. you don’t have to go to rallies and protests. people like this are why taylor was so scared to be vocal about her political opinions. she says something? wrong. she doesn’t say something? wrong. she’ll never please people like this, and honestly, i don’t think she wants to.

taylor swift cares more about her fans than any other artist i know. she comes to our houses and bakes us cookies. she invites us into her OWN HOME, just because she actually likes to hang out with fans. she spends hours and hours meeting people after shows FOR FREE because SHE. WANTS. TO. you can not say that taylor doesn’t care about her fans. if taylor didn’t care about her fans, meet and greets would be paid, or, most likely, wouldn’t happen at all. she wouldn’t invite people over to hear her music before the rest of the world. you CAN NOT say that taylor doesn’t care about her fans.

and, as far as taylor not being generous, here’s a list:

https://www.google.com/amp/s/www.billboard.com/amp/articles/news/8481430/timeline-taylor-swift-generosity

in conclusion, if you don’t know what you’re talking about, keep your mouth shut.😘
